The '''16th [[National Geographic Bee]]''' was held in [[Washington, D.C.]] on May 26, 2004, sponsored by the [[National Geographic Society]] and [[ING Group|ING]]. The final competition was moderated by [[Jeopardy!]] host [[Alex Trebek]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2013/05/130522-national-geography-bee-alex-trebek-2013-jeopardy/|title=Alex Trebek: On Hosting the National Geographic Bee|author=Melody Kramer|work=National Geographic}}</ref> The winner was [[Andrew Wojtanik]] of [[Kansas]], who won a $25,000 college scholarship, lifetime membership in the [[National Geographic Society]], and a trip to a [[Busch Gardens]]/[[SeaWorld Parks & Entertainment|Sea World]] Adventure Camp. The 2nd-place winner, Matthew Wells of [[Montana]], won a $15,000 scholarship. The 3rd-place winner, Eric Liaw of [[Hawaii]], won a $10,000 scholarship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2004/05/0526_040526_beechamp2004.html|title=Kansas Student Wins 2004 National Geographic Bee|author=Jennifer Vernon|work=National Geographic News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infoplease.com/ipa/A0922002.html|title=2004 Geography Bee|work=infoplease.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/5069057/ns/technology_and_science-science/t/-year-old-kansan-wins-geography-bee/#.WKHgRVUrJt8|title=14-year-old Kansan wins geography bee|author=Aparna H. Kumar|work=NBC News}}</ref>

