The border between China and Mongolia is the line that limits the territory of [[China|People's Republic of China]] and [[Mongolia]]; it stretches 4677 kilometers from east to west, between two triple borders [[China]] - [[Mongolia]] - [[Russia]] .

The west end is located 55&nbsp;km from the beginning of the border [[Russia]] - [[Kazakhstan]] and is marked by the mountains of [[Altai Mountains|Altai]] . In the east it is the [[Manchuria]]n border and passes through the [[Gobi Desert]] .

