{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Delaneys Falls | photo = Delaneys Falls.jpg | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = Delaneys Falls, in 2006 | map = Tasmania | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|41|16|48|S|146|03|36|E|region:AU-TAS_type:waterbody_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=ga1>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Delaneys Falls (TAS)|feature=TAS14785}}</ref><ref name=ga2>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Preston Falls (TAS)|feature=TAS14874}}</ref> | location = [[North West Tasmania|North West]] [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]] | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Plunge]] | elevation = | height = {{convert|25|m}}<ref name=wow>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-preston-falls.html|title=Preston Falls (Delaney's Falls)|work=World of Waterfalls|date=27 November 2006|accessdate=31 May 2014|publisher=Johnny T. Cheng}}</ref> | height_longest = | number_drops = 3 | width = | average_width = | watercourse = | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Delaneys Falls''', dually{{endash}}named<ref name=ga1/><ref name=ga2/> as the '''Preston Falls''', a [[Waterfall#Types|plunge waterfall]] on an unnamed watercourse, is located in the [[North West Tasmania|North West]] region of [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]].
==Location and features== The waterfall descends from the a ridge above the Gunns Plains, and descends approximately {{convert|25|m}}<ref name=wow/> and flows into the [[Leven River (Tasmania)|Leven River]] near the village of [[Gunns Plains, Tasmania|Gunns Plains]]. The falls is signposted as Preston Falls. There is a well kept [[Trail#Walking trail|walking track]] from the ridge down to the lookout. It's also possible to walk to the base; however there is no formalised track.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://bushwalk.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=3&t=10549 |title=Preston & Delaneys Falls |publisher=Bushwalk Australia |date=5 August 2012}}</ref>
