[[Category:Districts of the Republic of the Congo| ]] [[Category:Subdivisions of the Republic of the Congo]] [[Category:Lists of country subdivisions|Congo, Republic of, Districts]] [[Category:Country subdivisions in Africa|Congo, Republic of 2]] [[Category:Second-level administrative country subdivisions|Districts, Congo, Republic of]] [[Category:Republic of the Congo geography-related lists]]

The '''Grand Etang and Annandale Forest Reserves''' are contiguous protected areas located in the south central interior mountains of [[Grenada]]. Together they encompass the largest declared terrestrial [[protected area]] in Grenada followed by the [[Mount St. Catherine Forest Reserve]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oas.org/dsd/publications/Unit/oea51e/oea51e.pdf|title=Plan and Policy for a System of National Parks and Protected Areas|author1=Hubber, R. |lastauthoramp=yes |author2=Vincent, G |year=1988}}</ref>. The Grand Etang and Annandale Forest Reserves are managed together <ref>{{cite web|author1=Turner, M. |lastauthoramp=yes |year=2008 |url=http://parkscaribbean.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Annandale%20and%20Grand%20Etang%20Forest%20Reserves%20Management%20Plan%20(2007).pdf|title=Annandale and Grand Etang Forest Reserves Management Plan }}</ref>.
