{{Infobox mountain | name = Monte Caburaí | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 1465 | elevation_ref = | listing = | location = [[Roraima]], [[Brazil]] - [[Guyana]] | range = | coordinates = {{coord|05|16|20|N|60|12|43|W|type:mountain|display=inline,title}} | topo = | easiest_route = }}
[[Image:Caburaí-Chuí.png|thumb|right|220px|Location of Mount Caburaí in Brazil, in opposition to the country's southernmost point, [[Barra do Chuí]].]]
'''Monte Caburaí''' is a [[mountain]] located on the border between the [[South America]]n countries of [[Brazil]] and [[Guyana]] standing at {{convert|1465|m|ft|0}} above sea level. The source of the [[Uailã River|Uailã]] or Ailã river, located on the mountain, is the northernmost point of Brazil.
